G = nx.Graph()

edge_labels={}

def doDraw(node1, node2, logLine):
  
  print("pair: {} <--> {}".format(node1, node2))
  
  if(not G.has_edge(node1,node2)):
    storedLines = []
    storedLines.append(logLine)
    

    G.add_edge(node1, node2, weight=1, title=1, subtitle='testing', color='b', stored = storedLines)
    edge_labels = nx.get_edge_attributes(G, 'title')
    
    
  else:
    ed = G.get_edge_data(node1,node2)
    conn = int(ed["title"])
    conn = conn + 1
    
    c = 'b'
    
    if (conn > min_threshold):
      c = 'g'
      
    if (conn > ave_threshold):
      c = 'y'
      
    if (conn > top_threshold):
      c = 'r'
    
    storedLines = ed["stored"]
    #print(storedLines)
    G.remove_edge(node1,node2)
    
    if(not logLine in storedLines):
      storedLines.append(logLine)
    

    G.add_edge(node1, node2, weight=conn/10, title=conn, subtitle='testing', color=c, stored = storedLines)
    edge_labels = nx.get_edge_attributes(G, 'title')
    
  return G, edge_labels
